title: 7-AAA, 9-A volleyball brackets set
text:

Posted! A link has been posted to your Facebook feed. Join the Conversation Tom Kreager, tkreager@dnj.com 9:08 a.m. CDT October 2, 2015 
volleyball ball (Photo: Ruggiero_S, Getty Images/iStockphoto) 
MURFREESBORO – Siegel and Riverdale earned the top two seeds respectively in next week’s District 7-AAA volleyball tournament, which will be held Wednesday and Thursday at Stewarts Creek High School. 
Siegel finished 12-0 and didn’t drop a game against a league opponent for the second consecutive season. 
Seventh-seed La Vergne faces sixth-seed Smyrna at 4 p.m. Wednesday in the opening game of the tournament. Fourth-seed Oakland faces host Stewarts Creek, the fifth seed, at 5:30 p.m. 
Third-seed Blackman plays the La Vergne-Smyrna winner afterward at 7 p.m. 
Top-seed Siegel faces the Oakland-Stewarts Creek winner at 4 p.m. Thursday. Second-seed Riverdale plays the winner of Wednesday’s night cap at 5:30 p.m.. Both winners then meet at 7 p.m. in the championship. 
There will be a District 7-AAA junior varsity tournament on Monday and Tuesday at Stewarts Creek. Siegel and Blackman earned the top teams. 
District 9-A 
Eagleville won the District 9-A regular-season title and will be the top seed in its tournament, which begins Monday at MTCS. 
Eagleville plays fourth-seed Fayetteville at 6 p.m. Second-seed MTCS plays third-seed Community afterward at 7:30 p.m. 
The two winners then play at 6 p.m. Tuesday in the championship game. 
Reach Tom Kreager at 615-278-5168 and on Twitter @Kreager. 
District 7-AAA 
At Stewarts Creek 
Wednesday: 6 Smyrna vs. 7 La Vergne, 4 p.m.; 4 Oakland vs. 5 Stewarts Creek, 5:30 p.m.; 3 Blackman vs. (Smyrna-La Vergne winner), 7 p.m. 
Thursday: Siegel vs. (Oakland-Stewarts Creek winner), 4 p.m.; Riverdale vs. Blackman-(Smyrna-La Vergne winner) winner, 5:30 p.m., Championship, 7 p.m. 
District 9-A 
Monday: 1 Eagleville vs. 4 Fayetteville, 6 p.m.; 2 MTCS vs. 3 Community, 7:30 p.m.
